# Typography

## Tabular and numeric styling

Do **not** add `tabular-nums`, `lining-nums`, `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`, `font-mono` for numbers, or similar fixed-width numeric styling unless the user explicitly asks for it.

Default body and UI copy should use proportional figures so text reads naturally (e.g. countdowns, labels, wallet amounts in prose).

### When tabular styling is appropriate (only if requested)

- Aligned columns of numbers (ledger amounts, stat tables)
- OTP/PIN digit inputs where fixed-width alignment is a deliberate UX choice
- Monospace data displays (tokens, hashes, codes)

### Examples

```heex
<%# ✅ Default — proportional %>
<span class="font-semibold text-warning">{@countdown}</span>

<%# ❌ Do not add unless asked %>
<span class="tabular-nums font-semibold">{@countdown}</span>
```
